SIMPLE: mastery
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mastery
<hw>Mas"ter*y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Masteries</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[OF.
<ets>maistrie</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The position or authority of a master; dominion;
command; supremacy; superiority.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>If divided by mountains, they will fight for the
<qex>mastery</qex> of the passages of the tops.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W.
Raleigh.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Superiority in war or competition; victory; triumph;
preeminence.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The voice of them that shout for <qex>mastery</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Ex. xxxii. 18.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Every man that striveth for the <qex>mastery</qex> is temperate in
all things.</q> <rj><qau>1 Cor. ix. 25.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>O, but to have gulled him⟦br⟧
Had been a <qex>mastery</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>B. Jonson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Contest for superiority.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Holland.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>A masterly operation; a feat.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I will do a <qex>maistrie</qex> ere I go.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <specif>Specifically,</specif> <def>the philosopher's
stone.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>6.</sn> <def>The act process of mastering; the state of having
mastered.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He could attain to a <qex>mastery</qex> in all languages.</q>
<rj><qau>Tillotson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The learning and <qex>mastery</qex> of a tongue, being unpleasant
in itself, should not be cumbered with other difficulties.</q>
<rj><qau>Locke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mastful</ent>⟦br⟧
